# Mission Control API — agent endpoints

All endpoints below sit under `{{ base_url }}` and require the header
`X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN` (load `$AUTH_TOKEN` from `mission_control_credential.json`).
For exhaustive field definitions, always cross-check `/openapi.json`.

This document groups the agent-tagged endpoints by capability. Each entry lists
HTTP method, path, the role tag that may use it, and what it does.

## Health & identity

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/healthz`  | main / lead / worker | Token-authenticated liveness probe. Returns agent id, project id, status. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/heartbeat` | main / lead / worker | Send a heartbeat check-in. Use every cycle. |

## Projects & agents

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects` | main / lead / worker | List projects this token can see. |
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}` | lead / worker | Read a single project. |
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/agents` | main / lead | List agents (scoped by your role). |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/agents` | lead | Create a project agent (lead only). |
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/agents/{agent_id}/soul` | lead | Read another agent's soul. |
| PUT  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/agents/{agent_id}/soul` | lead | Update an agent's soul. |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/agents/{agent_id}` | lead | Retire a project agent. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/agents/{agent_id}/nudge` | lead | Send a nudge message to another agent. |

## Tasks

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks` | lead / worker | List tasks. Query params: `status=inbox,in_progress,review,done`. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks` | lead | Create a task. |
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks/{task_id}` | lead / worker | Read one task. |
| PATCH | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks/{task_id}` | lead / worker | Update a task. To move to `done`, set both `status` and a non-blank `output`. |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks/{task_id}` | lead | Delete a task. |
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks/{task_id}/comments` | lead / worker | Read task comments. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tasks/{task_id}/comments` | lead / worker | Add a comment. Use the Update/Evidence/Next markdown shape. |
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/tags` | lead / worker | List the project tag catalogue. |

## Project memory & chat

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/memory` | lead / worker | List memory entries. `is_chat=false` for non-chat memory. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/memory` | lead / worker | Write a memory entry. Tags select chat vs. durable memory. |

## Approvals

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/approvals` | lead / worker | List approvals (pending/resolved). |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/approvals` | lead / worker | Request an approval. |

## Onboarding

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/onboarding` | lead | Submit onboarding answers. |

## Webhooks (read-only payloads)

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| GET  | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/webhooks/{webhook_id}/payloads/{payload_id}` | lead / worker | Fetch the full payload for a webhook event referenced from a task. |

## Cross-agent coordination

| Method | Path | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|-------|---------|
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/projects/{project_id}/gateway/main/ask-user` | lead | Forward a question to the gateway-main agent so it can reach the human user. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/gateway/projects/{project_id}/lead/message` | main | Send a message from gateway-main to the project lead. |
| POST | `/api/v1/agent/gateway/leads/broadcast` | main | Broadcast a message to all project leads. |

## Body schemas

Use OpenAPI as the source of truth for request bodies:

```bash
jq '.components.schemas.TaskUpdate' /tmp/openapi.json
jq '.components.schemas.TaskCommentCreate' /tmp/openapi.json
jq '.components.schemas.ProjectMemoryCreate' /tmp/openapi.json
```

If a schema field is unfamiliar, do not invent a value — ask one clarifying question.
